title: For Sale:  Ballester Molina 1911 Argentina .45
postcontent: Very Nice what I think to be arsenal refinished parkarized Ballester Molina with very nice barrel. Barrel is bright and shiny with excellent riflings. The Serial number 118XX. The Ballester-Molina pistol was designed and built by the Argentine company Hispano Argentina Fábrica de Automotores SA (HAFDASA). The Ballester was originally called the Ballester-Rigaud (c. 1938–1940). The Ballester was designed to offer to the Argentinian police and military a less-expensive alternative to the Pistola Colt Modelo 1927, a licensed copy of the Colt M1911A1 built under the supervison of Colt engineers. Production of the Ballester-Molina began in 1938 and ceased in 1953. The history of the company dates back to 1929, when two Spanish entrepreneurs, Arturo Ballester and Eugenio Molina, established a branch of the Spanish Hispano-Suiza in Buenos Aires. Some years later, HAFDASA hired two engineers, the French Rorice Rigaud and Carlos Ballester-Molina, a relative of the founders. Rigaud became the chief designer of the firm, while Ballester-Molina was appointed chief executive officer. As the Ballester-Molina was designed to serve alongside the M1927 that was currently in Argentine service, it bears a striking resemblance to the Colt M1911A1. The Ballester-Molina and the M1911 share an identical 7-round magazine, barrel, recoil spring, and barrel bushing.  It's a great shooter!

Subcompact V3 laser by LaserLyte® is the company's most state-of-the-art, smallest and versatile rail mounted laser to date.  Now half the size of the previous model, the Subcompact V3 needs less than ¾-inch of Picatinny rail space to easily mount onto even the smallest firearms.

Constructed of T6 aluminum for extra strength and durability, this updated unit offers a smart, cost-effective auto-off feature. If left on for five minutes, the unit begins to display a unique flash for one minute, indicating to the user that the unit will automatically shut off soon. After one minute in flash mode the unit shuts itself off to extend battery life, prevent accidental activation and battery depletion. Press the unit's button at any time to reset this feature for five more minutes.

The Subcompact V3 easily mounts with a hex drive crossbar screw and features windage adjustment, elevation adjustment and programmable constant on and pulse modes. Additionally, the unit is ideal for left- and -right handed shooters with two separate activation buttons located on the backside of the laser. Not only will the laser fit nicely on the smallest of sub-compact railed pistols, it works great on modern rifles as well.

The Subcompact V3 laser is powered by four 377 batteries that provide five hours in constant on mode and ten hours in pulse mode of normal usage. Normal usage is defined as one minute on and one minute off. This test mimics actual usage where the unit is turned on and off and the battery is given time to automatically regenerate.

title: For Sale:  M-11 9mm Semi/Full Auto Double Threaded Barrel
postcontent:
If you want the versatility of a standard 3/4x10 9mm thread and also want a 1/2x28 thread, then this is the barrel for you!!!!

The barrel is super easy toninstal. My first one I put on took m about 12-15 mins' but on my last MAC it took 4 mins to change the barrel. Its just a super well built easy to work with and has all the treads you'd ever need to have. I have them on all my MACs and M-11's. I just order one too many this last order, my fault will end up your win!

This barrel is very cool because it allows you to have multiple threads on just 1 high quality made barrel. I have them on all my SMG MAC and the first one i installed is still on and probably close to 24-28k rounds through it and still as accurate and has not faded any since the day it was installed. That's why I have them on all 6 of my SMG's .

For the barrel being sold, I opened the package to make sure it was perfect in aesthetics and to check the thread quality. At this time i felt the threads and they are very smooth with no rough marks. I tested the 1/2x28 threads with my AAC Ti-Rant 9 and it fit perfectly and snug on the 1/2x28 threads. I then checked my Bowers Group CAC Suppressor on the barrels other threads, the 3/4x10 threads and they fit tight and smooth as well. It truly is one of the best threaded barrels I own. I can honestly its just as good if not better that some of my several hundred dollar Jarvis Barrels I use on my high end pistols. If I'd had known about these sooner, I have no doubt I'd have them on more pistols.

It truly is a GREAT GREAT DEAL !

The 1/2x28 threads are standard on .22 as well as on a standard 9mm barrel so you can thread on suppressors and muzzle brakes. The other thread ¾ X 10 is the standard thread for the M10/9 and M11/9 which will also fit any sub gun silencer like Gemtechs Viper or Bowers CAC, just to name a few. This Barrel Fits any MAC, M/10, M-11 SMG, Semi Auto and MPA mid sized 9mm.

title: For Sale:  Hi-Lux CMR 1-4x24mm Green Reticle
postcontent:
Hi-Lux doesn’t believe a true military grade tactical scope should be prohibitively expensive. So using the real world experience of Special Operations combat veterans, competition shooters and sportsman we developed our 1-4x24mm CMR (Close Medium Range). This highly flexible design offers great speed up close yet precision at longer distances. With a magnification range starting at 1x it allows a rifleman to keep both eyes open, like a red dot sight, during tactical situations or when hunting dangerous game. Increasing the magnification to 4x allows distant targets to be identified, ranged and engaged. 

This combination of capabilities makes for a far more flexible and useful optic than competing red dot sights, fixed power scopes or larger and heavier designs. Built on a compact yet robust 30mm tube, the CMR doesn’t add unnecessary bulk or weight to your rifle. Due to this the CMR is the perfect match for tactical and hunting rifles. In keeping with our name, the optical performance of the CMR is excellent. High quality fully multi-coated lenses are utilized to provide a clear and sharp image. Use in low light conditions hasn’t been overlooked and light transmission is the best in its class. 

An extremely practical circular reticle aids in quick target acquisition by drawing the attention of the shooter’s eye to the center of the scope. This allows extremely rapid engagement of close-range targets. To insure targets are easily visible when scanning, the Bullet Drop Compensating illuminated reticle is uncluttered and easy to use. The upper half of the Field of View remains clean and uncluttered for unimpeded observation. To allow rapid engagement of distant targets without touching the elevation turret, short bar aiming points calibrated for standard 5.56mm and 7.62mm service ammo are provided. 

The reticle also provides quick ‘no-math’ rangefinding of distant targets. Plus red or green reticle illumination is available. If a rifleman has time, ballistic adjustments can be dialed in using the CMR’s low-profile uncapped finger adjustable turrets. The single-rotation turrets provide audible and tactical adjustments and features Leatherwood’s new “Zero Locking System”, which does exactly what it says. Once the shooter has the scope sighted in, this system allows that alignment to be locked in place. A rheostat allows easy adjustment of the illuminated reticle’s intensity and provides Night Vision settings for use with Night Vision Devices. Our 1-4x CMR scope was built to survive in the toughest of conditions, a military environment. 

It has successfully passed abusive European military testing not only mounted on a rifle, but on a General Purpose Machine Gun as well. Other features include tough, wear resistant Perma-Coat soft luster blue-black finish, lenses polished to photographic quality, “Tri-Center” spring tension for positive windage and elevation adjustment, and a Fast Focus large diameter ocular lens. Hi-Lux’s CMR scope offers exceptional performance at a shockingly affordable price. About Hi-Lux Optics: Hi-Lux Optics’ roots reach back to the ART series of sniper scopes adopted by none other then the United States Army and successfully fielded during the Vietnam War. The top scoring sniper of this conflict utilized an ART scope designed by one of our founders, Jim Leatherwood. 

Over the years Hi-Lux Optics has developed innovative optical sights for the sportsman, competitive shooter and armed professional. Today Hi-Lux Optics has assembled a team of highly skilled engineers from the US, Europe and Asia to develop and manufacture a new generation of high quality military grade optics at affordable prices. Our goal is a simple one, to be recognized as China’s first premium optics manufacturer building high quality optics you can be proud of and rely on.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Mauser M2 .40 s&w pistol, new
postcontent:
The Mauser M2 is a Mauser branded handgun which is offered in the United States by Sig Sauer. It is a self-loading double-action pistol offered in .45 ACP initially, and later in .40 S&W and .357 SIG. The Mauser M2 is dimensionally similar to the SIG P229 pistol, also manufactured by Sig Sauer. Unlike most SIGs, it utilizes a rotating barrel like a Beretta. It's also striker-fired, like a Glock pistol.
 Mauser is a German arms manufacturer 
The M2 by Mauser could arguably be called "the safest handgun on the market today". Several safety features are integrated into the M2's design. The pistol features a loaded chamber indicator on top of the slide, which provides a visual indication that a round is present in the firing chamber. The pistol's magazine disconnect is designed to prevent the. pistol from being fired with the magazine removed from the pistol, even if a live round remains in the chamber. The pistol is equipped with an automatic firing pin safety that will not release the firing pin unless the trigger has been pulled. A disconnector prevents out of battery firing. The double-action only fire control system (in conjunction with the striker firing system) holds the striker at half cock which will not fire the cartridge should it be accidentally released. The manual external safety, located on the back of the slide, allows the owner to quickly observe if the handgun in is the safe mode while in the holster and can be quickly operated with the shooting hand.

Mauser M2 Technical Specifications:
 Mechanical rotary-action bolt; Striker-fired (no hammer); Double-action only semiautomatic pistol; loaded chamber indicator, magazine safety disconnect, manual safety, .40 S&W caliber.

Caliber: .40 S&W 
Action: recoil operated semi-automatic 
Trigger: double-action only (DAO) 
Safety: manual safety

title: For Sale:  Optima Elite: .50ML, .45/70, & 223
postcontent:
CVA Optima Elite with three barrels:


.50 cal 209 muzzleloader - fiber optics sighted in and ready to hunt now through Nov 2 in Zone C


on Nov 3, switch to the 45/70 barrel for deer and hogs (or GA bear)


and there's a .223 barrel for 'yotes and other varmints


Pair this with a good revolver (https://floridaguntrader.com/index.php?a=2&b= 220414) and you're set to hunt.


ML barrel is .50 cal Bergara, rated to 150gr black powder.  I think it's 29 inches long, so you get a full powder burn with pellets.  Has only been used with Triple Se7en pellets at 80, 90, and 100gr loads behind 275 and 295gr powerbelts and powerbelt clones.  [By the way, you might be able to use this to hunt hogs during small game season, too, when centerfire rifles are prohibited but not ML.]  This barrel is long to get a complete burn on 150 grains, so it also absorbs recoil well and shoot very precisely.  I've hunted three seasons with this.  Great rifle but with age I need something lighter for next year.


Haven't hunted the 24 inch 45/70, just fired 405gr cowboy loads at the range.  Fires a supersonic bullet weighing more than twice what a 30-06 would.  That's knockdown power.  With the ML recoil pad, these are almost as comfortable to shoot as a 150gr 30-30.  


.223 also just range practice and only a handful of rounds.  Not really my caliber.  This barrel and the 50 came with the original rifle.  This barrel is .223, not .5.56, and has 1 in 10 twist, so it's really for varminting with 35gr to 55gr bullets.  Hornady ammo with NTX and V-Max should shoot better from this barrel than from a standard 1 in 9 AR. Price is negotiable if you are a veteran or member of NRA but be reasonable.
More pics available.  The extra scope rail is included.  The scope in the photo is a beat up old BSA 3-12x50 from an older rifle I no longer have but the scope still holds zero on the 45/70.  You can have that at no extra charge.

As a knife enthusiast, you may be "in the know" about Ganzo, Enlan, Bee, and Sanrenmu knives. For those of you who are not, let me explain. 

These little known knife manufacturers are credited with making some very high quality, well designed yet affordable folder knives especially suited for every day carry purposes. In fact if you have any contacts within the knife/cutlery trade you will find out that Ganzo, Sanrenmu and Enlan's other activities include manufacturing knives for numerous western brands such as Benchmande, Spyderco, Buck, and SOG. So believe me when I say you're getting a lot for your money with a Ganzo blade.

Like Sanrenmu's line, the Ganzo brand can go head to head with many other, more expensive folders...many costing up to five times as much. That's what make these great EDC knives such an amazing find! 

If you're a Benchmade fan the Ganzo G711 is an EDC knife to take a look at. Just released, this is a very high value budget alternative to the Benchmade Mini Onslaught...and for a FRACTION of the price. Equipped with a swooping G10 handle design, a 440C stainless steel blade, and an Axis Lock locking system the Ganzo G711 offers a lot of bang for the buck.

So if you're looking for a solidly built, high quality, and affordable every day carry knife, look no further....now you're "in the know".
